data.description: *24-HOUR FROR* Welcome to this beautiful home in sought after McRae Trace subdivision. Custom built in 2006, this craftsman style brick home is located close to shopping, restaurants, entertainment, and top-rated schools. Greet guests in the open spacious foyer area and WOW them with this fantastic open floor plan home that features polished Brazilian cherry wood floors in all rooms except the kitchen, breakfast area, laundry, and bathrooms. On the left is the formal dining room featuring polished Brazilian cherry wood floors, crown molding, wainscoting, and a new chandelier, all of which will make festive meals elegant and inviting. Straight ahead is the great room with a corner gas log fireplace to keep the chill off on rare cool Southern evenings. Eyes will be drawn up to the beautiful coffered 10' ceilings that add elegance and ambiance. The double windows let lots of natural light flood the area and provides a view of the oversized back yard. The breakfast area is open to the great room and features tile flooring. crown molding, a trey ceiling, and double windows. Imagine the casual meals that will be lingered over and enjoyed while the events of the day are discussed. A granite topped step up breakfast bar where a quick snack can be enjoyed is the only separation from the kitchen. The chef of the family will delight in the granite countertops, loads of pretty custom cabinets, stainless appliances, a gas cooktop, and custom range hood all with a view of the great room. Double doors lead to a walk-in pantry large enough that a shopping trip may be necessary. When the day is done, retreat to the oversized primary bedroom where the wood flooring and crown molding add elegance along with the trey ceiling and recessed lighting. The ensuite bath has a his and her double vanity with custom sinks, a walk in shower for getting ready in the morning and a corner jetted tub to soak away the stresses of the day. There is a separate water closet and a fabulous walk around closet that provides enough room for all of today's wardrobes. On this side of the home is also a guest bedroom with crown molding, wood flooring, and plenty of natural light. Just outside the bedroom door is a full bath with custom granite topped vanity and a tub shower that is also a convenient location for visiting family and friends. On the opposite side of the home are two more nice sized bedrooms that continue with the same moldings and flooring as the rest of the home. Both rooms have nice sized closets with one bedroom having built in shelving. These two bedrooms are separated by a jack and jill bath that has granite topped vanity, copper sinks, and a tub shower combination that is separate from the vanity area so that more than one person could use the bathroom at the same time. On this side of the home and on the way to the garage is the laundry/mud room with custom cabinetry to store all the necessary laundry supplies. The oversized double garage is a side entry garage with a laundry sink and room for storage cabinets and a work bench for the handy person in the family. Off the great room is a wonderful screened porch where morning coffee can be enjoyed or a cool glass of tea while watching the sun set. There is also a patio for that evening barbeque with family and friends. The oversized privacy fenced backyard is a great place for whatever sport activity may be on the agenda and will be Fido's delight. There is a large outside storage building for storing lawn and gardening equipment and all the holiday decorations. This home features a front and back yard sprinkler system, a new HVAC system in 2021, a new water heater in 2019, and many more amenities that a personal tour will reveal. Come visit and fall in love. Listing agent is a licensed agent in the State of Alabama and related to the sellers. 2023-12-12
